Once an administrator has successfully validated their credentials and logged in, they are greeted with the Home screen. This screen displays a list of all previous schedules.
 Create New.. will open prompt the administrator for the name of the new schedule document to be created and it will open the blank document in a separate browser window or tab depending on your browser default settings. 
  Import will bring up a separate dialog box that allows the administrator to import a scheduling document from a CSV located on their hard drive  
  Throw Away Selected Documents will remove the selected document “Fall 2012” from the list of My Scheduling Documents and it will remove any subdocuments related to the document from th instructors view. It will warn the administrator before they delete if any subdocuments exist. The scheduling document can be viewed in “Trash”
  Merge Selected Documents will bring up a separate dialog box that allows the administrator to merge the resource data and schedules of multiple documents into a new schedule document

The New Schedule Document dialog will open prompt the administrator for the name of the new schedule document to be created and it will open the blank document in a separate browser window or tab depending on your browser default settings.  The Name Field indicates the new name for the scheduling document that will be created when the Create New.. button is pressed
  Create will open a new browser window/tab containing the blank schedule document
  Cancel will bring the administrator back to the Home screen

The Merge dialog allows the administrator to merge the resource data and schedules of multiple documents into a new schedule document
  The Name Field indicates the new name for the scheduling document that will be created when the Merge button is pressed
  Merge will open a new browser window/tab containing the combination of the schedule documents that were selected to be merged. 
  Cancel will bring the administrator back to the Home screen

If the Merge Selected Documents button is pressed and none of the scheduling documents are selected a warning is displayed letting the administrator know that they need to select at least two schedule documents in order to use the merge functionality
Please choose two or more schedule documents to merge.

After the administrator has chosen “Edit Default Day and Time Constraints” from the settings menu a dialog will be brought up that allows the administrator to change the days and times that courses are allowed to be scheduled for all newly created schedule documents

 OK will save the New Document Default Day and Time Constraints
 Cancel will bring the administrator back to the Home screen

The Settings Menu in the top right corner of the Home Screen allows the administrator to access and change the global settings affecting all newly created scheduling documents. 
 Edit Default Day and Time Constraints will bring up dialog box that allows the administrator to change the days and times that courses are allowed to be scheduled for all newly created schedule documents
  Manage Administrators will bring up a dialog box that allows the administrator to give other users administrator privileges

Edit Default Day and Time Constraints

After the administrator has chosen “Manage Administrators” from the settings menu a dialog will be brought up that allows the administrator to change the days and times that courses are allowed to be scheduled for all newly created schedule documents

 Add opens a new row so that you can type in a new username

Once an administrator clicks on the Courses button on the top menu they are greeted with the instructor overview screen
  New opens up a new row to add a course to the scheduling document
File      Settings       Courses   Instructors   Locations   Generate                                                                    Settings

Once an administrator clicks on the Instructors button on the top menu they are greeted with the instructor overview screen
  New opens up a new row to add an instructor to the scheduling document
  Gather Preferences... If an administrator wants to give instructors the opportunity to input their preferences using this application they will press this button. Upon pressing the Gather Preferences... button the Gather Instructor Preferences dialog opens.

While an administrator is editing the Instructors resource data, they may want to give instructors the opportunity to input their preferences using this application. Upon pressing the Gather Preferences... button the Gather Instructor Preferences dialog opens. 
  Time Checkbox Enabled will allow the instructors to submit time preferences for this schedule document
  Course Checkbox Enabled will allow the instructors to submit course preferences for this schedule document
  Distance Checkbox Enabled will allow the instructors to submit distance preferences for this schedule document
  Enable Preference Submission will open the gateway to allow the instructors to submit their preferences (while the instructors are disabled from submitting preferences, their Preference Status is set to “Not Enabled”)

While an administrator is editing the Instructors resource data, they may want to give instructors the opportunity to input their preferences using this application. Upon pressing the Gather Preferences... button the Gather Instructor Preferences dialog opens. 
  Time Checkbox Enabled will allow the instructors to submit time preferences for this schedule document
  Course Checkbox Enabled will allow the instructors to submit course preferences for this schedule document
  Distance Checkbox Enabled will allow the instructors to submit distance preferences for this schedule document
  Disable Preference Submission will close the gateway that allows the instructors to submit their preferences (while the instructors are allowed to submit preferences, their Preference Status is set to “Not Submitted” until they have pressed the “Submit” button in the instructor interface of the application)
 Send Reminder Email will open up a mailto link that allows the administrator to inform the instructors that they should submit their preferences

After entering the data in the resources tables, the administrator navigates to the Generate tab from the navigation bar and will be brought to this page to generate and edit the schedule
  Generate Schedule will run the schedule generation algorithm using all of the resources that are selected as “schedulable”
  Publish... brings up a dialog that allows the administrator to publish the schedule to PeopleSoft
  The Gray Bar with Arrows on the Left opens a side drawer with all of the courses from the Courses resource table

When an administrator double clicks on a scheduled course it brings up the Edit Course dialog box
  Ok saves the changes made to Course, Instructor, Location, and Time within the dialog box
  Cancel will bring the administrator back to the Generate screen
File      Settings       Courses   Instructors   Locations   Generate                                                                    Settings

This is the warning that an administrator will see if they click the Generate Schedule button without closing preferences
  Yes will ignore the warning and run the scheduling addict anyway
  Cancel will bring the administrator back to the Generate screen

Once an instructor has successfully validated their credentials and logged in, they are greeted with the Instructor Home screen. This screen displays a list of all scheduling documents and their associated preferences and schedules.
  Preferences will open up the instructor preferences wizard in a separate window/tab. If the button is red it indicates that the preferences have not been submitted for that scheduling document
  Schedule will open up a read only view of the schedule in a separate window/tab

Once an instructor has successfully validated their credentials and logged in, they are greeted with the Instructor Home screen. If the instructors administrator has not given an instructor permission to view any part of a scheduling document then this screen displays a message in the “My Scheduling Documents” window explaining that they should contact their administrator to access documents.
You do not have access to any documents, please contact your administrator, Kaylene Scanlon, for questions at krscanlo@calpoly.edu.

Once an instructor has pressed the Schedule button the application will open up a read only view of the schedule in a separate window/tab
  File/Open... will open the Home screen in a separate window/tab
  File/Print... will open up a separate window/tab with a printer friendly view of the calendar
  Email Admin... will open up a mailto link that allows the instructor to give feedback about the schedule to the administrator

Once an instructor has pressed the Preferences button the application will open up the instructor preferences wizard in a separate window/tab. 
  File/Open... will open the Home screen in a separate window/tab
  File/Print... will open up a separate window/tab with a printer friendly view of the instructors preferences
  File/Submit will submit the preferences for an administrator to view in their scheduling document
  Next is a navigation button that takes the instructor from the Course Preferences page to the Time Preferences page

Once an instructor has pressed the Next > button from course preferences, the application navigates to time preferences
 Next is a navigation button that takes the instructor from the Time Preferences page to the Distance Preferences page
 Back is a navigation button that takes the instructor from the Time Preferences page back to the Course Preferences page

Once an instructor has pressed the Next > button from time preferences, the application navigates to distance preferences
  Submit will submit the preferences for an administrator to view in their scheduling document
  Back is a navigation button that takes the instructor from the Distance Preferences page back to the Time Preferences page
Which building do you prefer to be nearest to? (building number)
